WEBVTT

00:09.810 --> 00:11.179
- * ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR

00:11.212 --> 00:13.047
* ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:13.081 --> 00:14.282
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:14.315 --> 00:22.290
*

00:28.296 --> 00:29.663
* ONE, TWO, DO IT

00:29.697 --> 00:32.133
*

00:32.166 --> 00:33.467
* ONE, TWO, THREE

00:33.501 --> 00:35.236
- * FOUR, FOUR

00:35.269 --> 00:38.339
*

00:40.108 --> 00:41.742
[cheers and applause]

00:41.775 --> 00:44.745
[Voodoo Princess]

00:44.778 --> 00:49.217
- * WILD PARTIES,
HEADS ARE SWIRLING *

00:49.250 --> 00:52.586
* GOTTA BE THE HOTTEST PLACE
AROUND *

00:52.620 --> 00:56.224
* LEGS ARE JUMPING
HIPS ARE ROLLING *

00:56.257 --> 00:59.260
* BEAUTIFUL BODIES
BOUNCING UP AND DOWN *

00:59.293 --> 01:02.563
* HOT SAPPHIC
SO GRAPHIC *

01:02.596 --> 01:06.234
* DANCE WITH FIRE
LIKE AN ISLAND GIRL *

01:06.267 --> 01:09.770
* HOT SAPPHIC
SO GRAPHIC *

01:09.803 --> 01:12.606
* DRINK FROM THE FOUNTAIN
AND GIVE IT A TWIRL *

01:12.640 --> 01:13.674
- HAVING FUN?

01:13.707 --> 01:15.409
- OH, IT'S AMAZING.
IT'S--

01:15.443 --> 01:17.678
- I DIDN'T REALIZE STAGETTE
PARTIES WERE THIS WILD.

01:17.711 --> 01:19.280
- IT'S THE WARM-UP
FOR YOUR HONEYMOON.

01:19.313 --> 01:22.183
NOW COME ON,
FOLLOW THE LEDA.

01:22.216 --> 01:24.152
THIS WAY.
- OH.

01:24.185 --> 01:27.421
[cheering]

01:27.455 --> 01:31.292
* WHEN SHE ROCKS
TUMULTUOUS *

01:31.325 --> 01:32.660
* WHEN SHE MOVES

01:32.693 --> 01:34.562
- [laughs]
- IS THIS THE HAPPY COUPLE?

01:34.595 --> 01:36.430
- SICKENING, ISN'T IT?

01:36.464 --> 01:38.499
THEY WANT THEIR FORTUNE TOLD.

01:38.532 --> 01:41.669
- PLEASE, I AM NOT A GYPSY...
ROSE LOUISE.

01:41.702 --> 01:43.837
I AM A TRAINED TAROTITIAN.

01:43.871 --> 01:46.340
- [chuckles]

01:46.374 --> 01:48.709
- NOW, SHALL WE SEE
WHAT THE CARDS HAVE IN STORE?

01:48.742 --> 01:50.344
- OH.
- OH.

01:51.645 --> 01:53.681
- UH-HUH.

01:53.714 --> 01:55.349
WHEN IS THE SPECIAL DAY?

01:55.383 --> 01:57.485
- THIS SATURDAY.

01:57.518 --> 01:58.586
- UH-OH.

01:58.619 --> 01:59.753
- WHAT?
- WHAT?

01:59.787 --> 02:01.389
- I'M SORRY, GIRLS,

02:01.422 --> 02:03.857
BUT YOU CAN'T POSSIBLY
GET MARRIED THIS SATURDAY.

02:03.891 --> 02:05.759
DIDN'T YOU KNOW?

02:05.793 --> 02:07.795
MERCURY IS IN RETROGRADE,

02:07.828 --> 02:11.365
A TIME OF EXTREME IMBALANCE
IN THE UNIVERSE,

02:11.399 --> 02:13.467
UPHEAVAL, MISCOMMUNICATION,

02:13.501 --> 02:14.435
AND MISUNDERSTANDINGS,

02:14.468 --> 02:17.471
RESULTING IN SERIOUS DISCORD
FOR EVERYONE.

02:17.505 --> 02:18.906
- UH--

02:18.939 --> 02:21.242
YEAH, BUT IS IT GOING
TO RAIN?

02:21.275 --> 02:22.042
- [sighs]

02:22.075 --> 02:24.412
SIGNING CONTRACTS,
MAKING PACTS,

02:24.445 --> 02:27.381
TAKING VOWS--
NO. NO. NOT NOW.

02:27.415 --> 02:29.850
IT'LL BE A TOTAL DISASTER.
A CATASTROPHE.

02:29.883 --> 02:32.886
BUT ON A POSITIVE NOTE,

02:32.920 --> 02:35.356
YOU'LL REDECORATE
YOUR DINING ROOM AROUND JUNE

02:35.389 --> 02:36.924
IN AQUA AND MAROON.

02:36.957 --> 02:40.728
AND IT WILL BE STUNNING.

02:40.761 --> 02:43.331
- AW.

02:43.364 --> 02:47.901
[pinball machine rings]

02:47.935 --> 02:49.537
- AH.

02:49.570 --> 02:52.240
SO WHAT DO YOU GET TWO DYKES
WHO HAVE EVERYTHING?

02:52.273 --> 02:53.907
- DYKES DON'T HAVE EVERYTHING.

02:53.941 --> 02:56.310
THAT'S WHY
THEY'RE SO MISERABLE.

02:56.344 --> 02:58.779
- WELL, UNFORTUNATELY,
MATCHING PENIS TRANSPLANTS

02:58.812 --> 03:02.283
ARE A LITTLE PRICY FOR
A POOR SHOPKEEPER LIKE MYSELF.

03:02.316 --> 03:03.851
- SILVER-PLATED DENTAL DAMS?

03:03.884 --> 03:06.754
- OOH, A SPECIALLY ENGRAVED
DOUBLE-HEADED DILDO?

03:06.787 --> 03:08.222
- HOW ABOUT STEMWARE?

03:08.256 --> 03:11.292
- HONEY, DILDOS ARE STEMWARE.
[all chuckling]

03:11.325 --> 03:12.593
- A WATER BUFFALO.

03:12.626 --> 03:14.262
- WHAT?

03:14.295 --> 03:15.929
- LESBIANS ARE
INTO ENDANGERED SPECIES.

03:15.963 --> 03:18.499
- YEAH, UNFORTUNATELY
THEY AREN'T ONE OF THEM.

03:18.532 --> 03:19.967
- OH, YOU GUYS ARE BRUTAL.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.303
- WE NEED TO GET THEM SOMETHING
THAT SHOWS WE CARE,

03:22.336 --> 03:23.437
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

03:23.471 --> 03:24.705
- WELL, I'D GO SHOPPING
WITH YOU,

03:24.738 --> 03:26.640
BUT, UH,
I'M ACTUALLY PICKING OUT

03:26.674 --> 03:29.577
A VERY SPECIAL GIFT
FOR MYSELF.

03:29.610 --> 03:30.711
YES, BOYS.

03:30.744 --> 03:32.313
I HAVE FINALLY SAVED UP
ENOUGH CASH

03:32.346 --> 03:34.315
WHACKING AWAY
ON TEDDY'S HOUSE OF PORN,

03:34.348 --> 03:36.717
TO BUY ME THAT BRAND-NEW ASS
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED.

03:36.750 --> 03:39.019
- YOU'RE REALLY GETTING
PLASTIC SURGERY?

03:39.052 --> 03:41.422
- THE LANDSCAPE IS LITTERED
WITH SLAVES TO BEAUTY

03:41.455 --> 03:42.956
WHO HAVE NOSES
THAT ARE TOO SMALL,

03:42.990 --> 03:44.592
TITS THAT ARE TOO BIG.

03:44.625 --> 03:46.560
YOU COULD END UP
THE NEXT COSMETIC CASUALTY.

03:46.594 --> 03:48.462
- IT'S TRUE.
WHAT IF THEY MAKE A MISTAKE?

03:48.496 --> 03:50.698
- LIKE ACCIDENTALLY SEWING UP
YOUR ASSHOLE?

03:50.731 --> 03:52.500
- WELL, YOU'LL JUST HAVE
TO CHEW ME A NEW ONE.

03:52.533 --> 03:53.967
YOU'RE SO GOOD AT IT.

03:54.001 --> 03:57.538
- AT LEAST WAIT A WEEK UNTIL
MERCURY'S OUT OF RETROGRADE.

03:57.571 --> 03:59.807
- BOY, YOU ACTUALLY BELIEVE
IN THAT SHIT?

03:59.840 --> 04:02.376
- THERE IS EVIDENCE THAT
UPHEAVALS IN OUR SOLAR SYSTEM

04:02.410 --> 04:04.345
CAN CAUSE DISTURBANCES
HERE ON EARTH.

04:04.378 --> 04:05.746
- BLAMING THE PLANETS
FOR YOUR FUCK-UPS

04:05.779 --> 04:09.717
IS JUST AN EXCUSE
NOT TO ACCEPT RESPONSIBILITY.

04:09.750 --> 04:12.019
[overlapping chatter]

04:12.052 --> 04:13.354
- GENTLEMEN!

04:13.387 --> 04:15.323
IT'S TIME TO PICK THE WINNER

04:15.356 --> 04:18.392
OF THE LIBERTY AVENUE AIDS
HOSPICE CHARITY RAFFLE.

04:18.426 --> 04:19.827
[cheers and applause]

04:19.860 --> 04:21.929
NOW SOMEBODY'S GOING ON
AN ALL-EXPENSE PAID TRIP FOR TWO

04:21.962 --> 04:25.666
TO THIS WEEKEND'S
WHITE PARTY IN MIAMI.

04:25.699 --> 04:27.067
CAN I GET A DRUM ROLL PLEASE?

04:27.100 --> 04:30.838
[all tapping]

04:32.473 --> 04:37.845
AND THE LUCKIEST PRICK
IN PITTSBURGH IS...

04:37.878 --> 04:39.680
BRIAN KINNEY.

04:39.713 --> 04:43.517
[cheers and applause]

04:43.551 --> 04:44.718
- YEAH, I DON'T KNOW.

04:44.752 --> 04:46.420
THE PLANETS DON'T SEEM TO BE
FUCKING WITH ME.

04:46.454 --> 04:47.321
[mockingly laughs]

04:47.355 --> 04:49.357
- OH, YEAH?
HOW DO YOU PLAN TO GO AWAY

04:49.390 --> 04:51.024
AND STILL BE AT
MELANIE AND LINDSAY'S WEDDING?

04:51.058 --> 04:52.926
[mocking laugh]

04:52.960 --> 04:55.929
[cheers and applause]

04:59.700 --> 05:01.935
- OH, NO.

05:01.969 --> 05:03.371
- VIC?

05:03.404 --> 05:05.839
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
- YOU OKAY, UNCLE VIC?

05:05.873 --> 05:09.510
- SEE FOR YOURSELF.

05:09.543 --> 05:11.612
- THEY'RE REEVALUATING
YOUR DISABILITY?

05:11.645 --> 05:13.614
- AND IF THEY TAKE IT AWAY,
THERE GOES MY SHARE

05:13.647 --> 05:14.882
OF OUR MONTHLY INCOME.

05:14.915 --> 05:16.784
- WELL, GOD DAMN IT!

05:16.817 --> 05:18.652
WHAT KIND OF
FUCKED UP UNIVERSE

05:18.686 --> 05:21.889
WOULD SNATCH MY BROTHER
FROM THE JAWS OF DEATH

05:21.922 --> 05:24.124
ONLY TO SLOWLY STARVE
BOTH OF US

05:24.157 --> 05:25.793
OUT OF HOUSE AND HOME?

05:25.826 --> 05:27.628
- BEN SAYS IT'S GOT TO DO
WITH MERCURY.

05:27.661 --> 05:28.696
- OH, DOES HE?

05:28.729 --> 05:31.399
- LOOK, DON'T PANIC.
I CAN HELP OUT.

05:31.432 --> 05:32.800
- NO.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.001
MICHAEL, THIS IS A SIGN.

05:34.034 --> 05:35.869
IF I LOSE MY BENEFITS, THEN...

05:35.903 --> 05:38.038
I'LL JUST HAVE
TO GET BACK TO WORK.

05:38.071 --> 05:39.773
- ARE YOU SURE?

05:39.807 --> 05:42.476
- ONCE UPON A TIME,
I WAS A PRETTY DECENT CHEF.

05:42.510 --> 05:44.378
- DECENT?
HAH.

05:44.412 --> 05:45.779
DECENT?

05:45.813 --> 05:47.748
HE WAS ANOTHER SARA LEE.

05:47.781 --> 05:49.450
- I'LL TAKE THAT
AS THE COMPLIMENT

05:49.483 --> 05:52.520
THAT I'M SURE WAS INTENDED.

05:52.553 --> 05:54.622
THE TRICK WILL BE FINDING
SOMEBODY WILLING TO HIRE ME.

05:54.655 --> 05:56.490
- WELL, THERE'S
NO SHORTAGE OF RESTAURANTS.

05:56.524 --> 05:58.826
- THERE'S ALSO
NO SHORTAGE OF CHEFS.

05:58.859 --> 06:00.861
I'M RUSTY AS AN OLD SKILLET.

06:00.894 --> 06:03.464
AND WHEN THEY FIND OUT
WHY I HAVEN'T BEEN WORKING,

06:03.497 --> 06:05.899
THEIR SOUFFLES WILL DROP.

06:05.933 --> 06:07.968
- WOULD YOU STOP TALKING
YOURSELF OUT OF A JOB

06:08.001 --> 06:12.906
BEFORE YOU EVEN GET ONE?

06:12.940 --> 06:15.809
WHAT IF I GOT YOU
A SHIFT AT THE DINER?

06:15.843 --> 06:18.145
WE COULD WORK TOGETHER.

06:18.178 --> 06:21.048
- [chuckles]

06:21.081 --> 06:22.616
- COME ON.

06:22.650 --> 06:24.885
IN SELECTING
YOUR IDEAL DERRIERE,

06:24.918 --> 06:27.488
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT THAT
YOU BE HAPPY WITH YOUR CHOICE,

06:27.521 --> 06:29.156
SINCE IT'LL BE FOLLOWING
YOU AROUND

06:29.189 --> 06:30.123
FOR A LONG, LONG TIME.

06:30.157 --> 06:31.124
- RIGHT.

06:31.158 --> 06:32.926
- OUR CATALOG WILL HELP.

06:32.960 --> 06:34.595
- THANKS.

06:34.628 --> 06:36.096
[phone rings]
[exhales]

06:36.129 --> 06:38.932
WOW.
SO MANY TO CHOOSE FROM.

06:38.966 --> 06:41.469
PEAR SHAPE, MELON SHAPE.

06:41.502 --> 06:45.673
EACH WITH
ITS OWN UNIQUE PERSONALITY.

06:45.706 --> 06:46.674
GOD.

06:46.707 --> 06:48.075
HOW AM I EVER GOING
TO DECIDE?

06:48.108 --> 06:51.812
- WELL, SOMETIMES IT HELPS
TO SEE THEM IN THE FLESH.

06:51.845 --> 06:53.814
MY STAFF HAVE
ALL HAD WORK DONE,

06:53.847 --> 06:54.948
AND THEY'D BE MORE
THAN WILLING TO SHOW YOU

06:54.982 --> 06:56.584
OUR MOST POPULAR MODELS.

06:56.617 --> 06:57.985
- SOMEBODY LOVES HIS JOB.

06:58.018 --> 06:59.019
[chuckles]

06:59.052 --> 07:00.721
- WHEN YOU WORK IN A BAKERY,

07:00.754 --> 07:02.089
IT'S HARD TO RESIST THE BUNS.

07:02.122 --> 07:03.524
[intercom beeps]

07:03.557 --> 07:05.926
GERALD?
TELL THE BOYS TO COME IN.

07:05.959 --> 07:07.728
- [over intercom]
YES, DOCTOR.

07:07.761 --> 07:10.731
[military marching band music]

07:10.764 --> 07:12.566
*

07:12.600 --> 07:13.801
- OH.

07:13.834 --> 07:18.105
*

07:18.138 --> 07:21.975
- MR. HONEYCUTT'S HAVING
DIFFICULTY MAKING UP HIS MIND.

07:27.548 --> 07:29.483
- WOW, THEY'RE ALL SO BEAUTIFUL.

07:29.517 --> 07:31.852
- I DID THEM ALL MYSELF.

07:31.885 --> 07:33.654
I ALSO DID THEIR ASSES.

07:33.687 --> 07:34.855
- OH.
[both laughing]

07:34.888 --> 07:36.256
- SO TAKE A GOOD, CLOSE LOOK.

07:36.289 --> 07:38.158
FEEL FREE TO TOUCH.

07:38.191 --> 07:41.829
FIRMNESS AND FLEXIBILITY
ARE KEY FACTORS.

07:41.862 --> 07:43.764
- DOUBLE BUBBLE.
- MM-HMM.

07:43.797 --> 07:46.166
- GOOD SKIN TONE.

07:46.199 --> 07:47.635
REALLY, UH,

07:47.668 --> 07:49.603
REALLY GIVES A BOY
SOMETHING TO...

07:49.637 --> 07:52.506
HOLD ON TO.

07:52.540 --> 07:54.274
OH. [laughs]
DIMPLES.

07:54.307 --> 07:56.276
ALL THE RAGE THIS YEAR.

07:56.309 --> 07:58.746
LOOKS LIKE
LITTLE TWIN PUDDINGS

07:58.779 --> 08:00.848
JUST BEGGING TO BE TASTED.

08:00.881 --> 08:03.784
OH, HELLO, GORGEOUS.

08:03.817 --> 08:05.953
WHOO! LOOK AT THAT.

08:05.986 --> 08:07.921
IT'S A GREAT GIVE, YOU KNOW?

08:07.955 --> 08:09.790
YOU COULD STRETCH IT OUT,

08:09.823 --> 08:11.291
AND IT'D STILL HOLD ITS SHAPE.

08:11.324 --> 08:12.726
[laughter]

08:12.760 --> 08:16.597
GOD, THEY'RE ALL SO TEMPTING,
DR. BEAMER.

08:16.630 --> 08:19.132
BUT HOW DO I KNOW
WHAT'LL LOOK GOOD ON ME?

08:19.166 --> 08:21.101
- I CAN SHOW YOU ON
MY DIGITAL IMAGING SYSTEM.

08:21.134 --> 08:22.803
OR IF YOU PREFER,

08:22.836 --> 08:23.871
WE CAN DO A CUSTOM DESIGN.

08:23.904 --> 08:25.606
OF COURSE,
THAT WOULD BE EXTRA.

08:25.639 --> 08:27.140
- WELL, NOW IS DEFINITELY
NOT THE TIME

08:27.174 --> 08:28.742
TO SIT ON ONE'S WALLET.

08:28.776 --> 08:30.744
LET'S DO IT.
- GOOD.

08:30.778 --> 08:33.280
- WE FAXED THOSE ORDERS
WEEKS AGO.

08:33.313 --> 08:36.116
NO.
WEEKS AGO.

08:36.149 --> 08:37.585
[sighs]

08:37.618 --> 08:38.886
MANY DAYS AGO.

08:38.919 --> 08:40.721
LOOK, IS THERE SOMEBODY THERE
WHO SPEAKS ENGLISH

08:40.754 --> 08:41.722
AS A FIRST LANGUAGE?

08:41.755 --> 08:42.723
- PARDON?

08:42.756 --> 08:45.158
- OH.
LINDSAY!

08:45.192 --> 08:48.195
OH, GOD. GUS JUST ATE
THE SEATING PLAN.

08:48.228 --> 08:49.763
- WE DO NOT HAVE THE ORDER.

08:49.797 --> 08:51.599
- SO, WHAT ARE YOU GOING
TO SERVE

08:51.632 --> 08:54.735
MY 24 NO DAIRY, NO YEAST,
NO WHEAT KOSHER VEGANS?

08:54.768 --> 08:56.069
- MADAME...
- OH--

08:56.103 --> 08:57.971
- [hyperventilating]

08:58.005 --> 08:58.972
- OH.
[phone beeps]

08:59.006 --> 09:02.209
[groans]
SWEETHEART, OH MY GOD.

09:02.242 --> 09:04.878
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

09:04.912 --> 09:08.816
- HAVE...A PANIC...

09:08.849 --> 09:09.817
ATTACK.

09:09.850 --> 09:11.719
- OH, MY GOD!

09:11.752 --> 09:13.787
- BLOATING. I--

09:13.821 --> 09:15.856
LOOK. I CAN'T EVEN...

09:15.889 --> 09:17.257
PUT ON MY SHOE.

09:17.290 --> 09:19.026
[hyperventilating]

09:19.059 --> 09:20.661
- IT'S--IT'S JUST
A LITTLE ANXIETY-RELATED

09:20.694 --> 09:21.662
WATER RETENTION.

09:21.695 --> 09:23.096
IT'S--
- [crying]

09:23.130 --> 09:28.101
I'M AS BIG AS LAKE MICHIGAN.
- NO, NO, NO, NO.

09:28.135 --> 09:29.770
- [rapid panting]
- NO, YOU'RE NOT.

09:29.803 --> 09:35.643
HERE. BREATHE INTO THIS.
THERE WE GO, THERE WE GO.

09:35.676 --> 09:37.778
THERE WE GO.
OKAY. LIE DOWN.

09:37.811 --> 09:39.179
PUT YOUR FEET UP.

09:39.212 --> 09:40.347
THAT'S IT.

09:40.380 --> 09:43.050
- [rapid panting]

09:43.083 --> 09:45.986
I AM NOT GOING TO GET
INTO MY DRESS.

09:46.019 --> 09:46.887
- YOU KNOW, I THOUGHT WE AGREED,

09:46.920 --> 09:48.656
NO WEIRD LESBO SEX
IN FRONT OF THE KID.

09:48.689 --> 09:50.323
both: FUCK OFF, BRIAN!

09:50.357 --> 09:51.792
- FINE. I JUST DROPPED
BY TO LET YOU KNOW

09:51.825 --> 09:52.926
I'M NOT GOING TO BE
AT THE WEDDING.

09:52.960 --> 09:54.828
- FUCK!
- I'M GOING TO THE WHITE PARTY

09:54.862 --> 09:55.963
IN MIAMI INSTEAD.
LATER.

09:55.996 --> 09:57.765
- YOU CAN'T DITCH
MY SPECIAL DAY!

09:57.798 --> 09:59.667
- YOU SELFISH PRICK.

09:59.700 --> 10:01.769
- AS USUAL,
OBJECTIVITY FALLS TO ME.

10:01.802 --> 10:02.636
THINK.

10:02.670 --> 10:04.772
YOU DON'T REALLY
WANT ME THERE, DO YOU?

10:04.805 --> 10:07.340
I'D HAVE TO BE CHEMICALLY
DEPENDENT JUST TO SHOW UP.

10:07.374 --> 10:09.142
I'LL BE DRUNK, I'LL BE BORED,

10:09.176 --> 10:11.712
NOT TO MENTION BETTER-LOOKING
THAN THE BRIDES.

10:11.745 --> 10:14.748
I'LL OFFEND ALL THE DYKES,
I'LL HECKLE THE CEREMONY,

10:14.782 --> 10:16.049
TABLE-DANCE AT THE RECEPTION,

10:16.083 --> 10:18.018
AND INEVITABLY FUCK
EVERY GOOD-LOOKING GUY,

10:18.051 --> 10:20.120
GAY, STRAIGHT, OR UNDECIDED
IN THE PLACE.

10:20.153 --> 10:24.257
FINALLY, I'LL PASS OUT NAKED,
BITCHING ABOUT THE CHEAP BOOZE.

10:24.291 --> 10:26.026
YOU'LL LOSE YOUR DIGNITY,
YOUR FRIENDS, AND YOUR SHIRTS

10:26.059 --> 10:27.327
PAYING FOR THE DAMAGES.

10:27.360 --> 10:29.262
HELL, I'M DOING YOU
A FAVOR

10:29.296 --> 10:32.065
GETTING OUT OF TOWN.

10:33.834 --> 10:36.369
both: HAVE A SAFE TRIP.
[Gus babbles]

10:41.008 --> 10:42.442
- [sighs]

10:42.475 --> 10:44.878
I CAN'T GO ON.

10:44.912 --> 10:46.346
WE'VE WALKED, HOW FAR?

10:46.379 --> 10:49.149
100 BLOCKS
IN, WHAT, 100 HOURS?

10:49.182 --> 10:51.284
- TRY TWO BLOCKS IN
ABOUT 11 MINUTES.

10:51.318 --> 10:52.419
- OH.

10:52.452 --> 10:55.055
SEEMS A LOT LONGER WHEN
YOU'RE SHOPPING FOR LESBIANS.

10:55.088 --> 10:57.791
- I STILL SAY A WEDDING GIFT
SHOULD BE SOMETHING ROMANTIC.

10:57.825 --> 10:59.359
YOU KNOW, LIKE THIS.

10:59.392 --> 11:01.228
- LINGERIE?

11:01.261 --> 11:03.330
I THOUGHT YOU SAID "ROMANTIC"?

11:03.363 --> 11:06.867
YOU WANT TO GET TWO DYKES
A ROMANTIC GIFT?

11:06.900 --> 11:08.268
GET THEM THIS.

11:08.301 --> 11:10.137
- POWER TOOLS?
THAT'S ROMANTIC?

11:10.170 --> 11:11.171
- FOR DYKES THEY ARE.

11:11.204 --> 11:12.372
[laughter]

11:12.405 --> 11:13.473
OH, AND FOR ONLY $499,

11:13.506 --> 11:15.909
THESE BEAUTIES ARE A STEAL.

11:15.943 --> 11:18.278
- ONLY?
I CAN BARELY AFFORD A SCREW.

11:18.311 --> 11:22.182
- WELL, FORTUNATELY,
YOU HAVE BEN.

11:22.215 --> 11:24.918
I'LL COVER IT, WE'LL JUST
SAY IT'S FROM BOTH OF US.

11:24.952 --> 11:27.220
- I CAN'T LET YOU DO THAT.
- I CAN AFFORD IT.

11:27.254 --> 11:28.822
[cell phone chirps]

11:28.856 --> 11:32.926
OH, SHIT.

11:32.960 --> 11:34.394
SHIT.
- WHAT?

11:34.427 --> 11:36.196
- I'D BETTER GET BACK
TO THE STUDIO.

11:36.229 --> 11:38.799
I'VE GOT A THREE-WAY
AT HALF PAST 4:00.

11:38.832 --> 11:40.801
OR IS IT A FOUR-WAY
AT HALF PAST 3:00?

11:40.834 --> 11:43.837
I CAN'T REMEMBER.
HERE. TAKE THIS.

11:43.871 --> 11:45.205
- WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO GET,

11:45.238 --> 11:48.776
THE POWER TOOLS OR THE LINGERIE?
- YOU DECIDE.

11:48.809 --> 11:51.812
WHATEVER YOU PICK, I'M SURE
IT'LL BE THE PERFECT GIFT.

11:51.845 --> 11:53.814
BYE.

12:03.456 --> 12:06.426
[tribal music]

12:06.459 --> 12:14.401
*

12:15.368 --> 12:16.837
- HELLO, MON!

12:16.870 --> 12:18.271
WELCOME.

12:18.305 --> 12:22.175
COME TAKE A LOOK HERE.

12:22.209 --> 12:24.277
- THESE ARE AMAZING.
WHERE ARE THEY FROM?

12:24.311 --> 12:27.781
- FROM A LITTLE COUNTRY
IN AFRICA RIGHT NEXT TO CHAD.

12:27.815 --> 12:29.149
IT'S CALLED CHUCK.

12:29.182 --> 12:31.484
MY PEOPLE HAVE LIVED THERE
FOR CENTURIES

12:31.518 --> 12:34.888
IN PEACE AND HARMONY,
MAKING LOVE AND ART.

12:34.922 --> 12:37.057
- HMM.

12:39.126 --> 12:41.394
- ISN'T SHE BEAUTIFUL?

12:41.428 --> 12:42.863
HER NAME IS HAZA-RI,

12:42.896 --> 12:46.033
GODDESS OF LOVE AND PRIDE.

12:46.066 --> 12:47.434
- HOW MUCH IS SHE?

12:47.467 --> 12:49.870
- $600.

12:49.903 --> 12:51.371
- I ONLY HAVE $500.

12:51.404 --> 12:53.974
- THAT WOULD BE
IN $600 CHUCK DOLLARS,

12:54.007 --> 12:55.508
$500 AMERICAN.

12:55.542 --> 13:00.080
*

13:00.113 --> 13:03.150
- COMPETITION: WORLD CLASS.

13:03.183 --> 13:05.418
WARDROBE: CRUCIAL.

13:05.452 --> 13:11.124
MARGIN FOR ERROR: ZERO.

13:11.158 --> 13:16.096
SO LONG, PITTSBURGH.
HELLO, MIAMI VICE.

13:20.968 --> 13:23.003
- I THOUGHT YOUR
ALL-EXPENSE PAID FUCK FEST

13:23.036 --> 13:25.105
WAS JUST FOR THE WEEKEND.

13:25.138 --> 13:26.606
- WELL, EACH PARTY HAS
ITS OWN THEME

13:26.639 --> 13:29.009
AND A STRICT DRESS CODE.

13:29.042 --> 13:30.844
THE WHITE PARTY--

13:30.878 --> 13:34.181
15,000 HORNY QUEERS
ALL IN WHITE.

13:34.214 --> 13:35.515
- I'LL BE BUSY, TOO.

13:35.548 --> 13:37.985
I HAVE A PAPER DUE
ON RENAISSANCE ART.

13:38.018 --> 13:40.153
- THEN THERE'S
THE MUSCLE BEACH PARTY.

13:40.187 --> 13:41.488
- THEN THERE'S THE LAUNDRY.

13:41.521 --> 13:43.590
AND OF COURSE THE WEDDING.

13:43.623 --> 13:46.193
- AND I MUSTN'T FORGET
THE CABANA BOY CONTEST.

13:46.226 --> 13:48.461
- I HAVE TO REMEMBER
TO WRITE MY GRANDMOTHER.

13:48.495 --> 13:50.063
- FUCK.

13:50.097 --> 13:52.565
I'VE GOT DICK-ALL TO WEAR
TO THE WHITE DAWN BASH.

13:52.599 --> 13:55.602
- WILL YOU EVEN NEED CLOTHES
BY THEN?

13:55.635 --> 13:58.005
- NOT IF YOU'VE GOT ANYTHING
TO SAY ABOUT IT.

13:58.038 --> 14:00.007
- YOU'RE TAKING ME?

14:00.040 --> 14:01.274
- IF YOU CAN TEAR
YOURSELF AWAY

14:01.308 --> 14:02.209
FROM YOUR GRANNY'S LETTER.

14:02.242 --> 14:03.977
- OH, THANK YOU!

14:04.011 --> 14:05.612
THANK YOU, THANK YOU,
THANK YOU!

14:05.645 --> 14:11.084
SHIT! WHAT AM I GONNA WEAR?

14:11.118 --> 14:13.887
- * WHAT DO YOU ASK OF ME?

14:13.921 --> 14:16.423
* I ASK ONLY

14:16.456 --> 14:18.658
* THAT YOU DANCE

14:18.691 --> 14:22.930
*

14:22.963 --> 14:25.365
- YOU ARE NOT GONNA BELIEVE
WHAT I GOT THEM.

14:25.398 --> 14:26.433
WHAT WE GOT THEM.
- WHAT? WHAT?

14:26.466 --> 14:28.201
WHAT IS IT?

14:28.235 --> 14:30.037
- NO, YOU'LL SEE,
IT'S A SURPRISE.

14:30.070 --> 14:32.072
WHAT'D YOU GET THEM?

14:32.105 --> 14:34.942
- THE BEST GIFT OF ALL--
MY ABSENCE.

14:34.975 --> 14:36.576
- ALL RIGHT, JUDGES.

14:36.609 --> 14:40.380
TIME TO MAKE
YOUR FINAL DECISION.

14:40.413 --> 14:46.053
WHICH OF THE FOLLOWING
THREE CHOICES WILL IT BE?

14:46.086 --> 14:47.154
- WELL, IF YOU CHOOSE
NUMBER ONE,

14:47.187 --> 14:49.356
YOU'LL LOOK EXACTLY
LIKE, UH...

14:49.389 --> 14:51.058
MICHAEL.

14:51.091 --> 14:52.125
- GO WITH NUMBER TWO.
- SHH.

14:52.159 --> 14:53.126
- YOU'LL LOOK JUST LIKE
THE REAR END

14:53.160 --> 14:54.494
OF A '72 IMPALA.

14:54.527 --> 14:57.230
- NUMBER THREE'S
PERT AND PERKY.

14:57.264 --> 14:59.632
THOUGH IT MIGHT BE TOO SMALL
FOR THE REST OF YOUR FEATURES.

14:59.666 --> 15:02.402
- PERHAPS I NEED
AN ARTIST'S OPINION.

15:02.435 --> 15:05.939
JUSTIN, WHICH DO YOU
FIND TO BE

15:05.973 --> 15:07.340
MOST AESTHETICALLY PLEASING?

15:07.374 --> 15:08.675
- [chuckles]

15:08.708 --> 15:11.344
- THIS ONE.

15:11.378 --> 15:13.280
IT SUCCESSFULLY INTEGRATES
FORM AND FUNCTION

15:13.313 --> 15:15.348
INTO AN ELEGANT WHOLE,
BUT AT THE SAME TIME,

15:15.382 --> 15:16.583
IT'S IN GOOD TASTE.

15:16.616 --> 15:18.685
- HE DOESN'T WANT AN ASS
WITH GOOD TASTE.

15:18.718 --> 15:22.055
HE WANTS AN ASS
THAT TASTES GOOD.

15:22.089 --> 15:24.992
- THANK YOU, SWEETHEART.

15:25.025 --> 15:27.594
WELL, BOYS,
SHALL WE DANCE?

15:27.627 --> 15:30.030
- I NEED MY BEAUTY REST
FOR THE WHITE PARTY.

15:30.063 --> 15:31.198
- NOW THAT YOU'RE OVER 30,

15:31.231 --> 15:32.699
SHOULDN'T YOU BE GOING
TO THE GRAY PARTY?

15:32.732 --> 15:34.034
- YOU SHOULD BE GOING

15:34.067 --> 15:36.336
TO MELANIE AND LINDSAY'S
WEDDING.

15:36.369 --> 15:39.639
- YOU'LL BE THERE,
YOU CAN CRY FOR BOTH OF US.

15:39.672 --> 15:41.474
* DANCE

15:41.508 --> 15:47.314
*

15:47.347 --> 15:48.715
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

15:48.748 --> 15:50.750
EVERY TIME SOMETHING BIG
HAPPENS,

15:50.783 --> 15:53.453
MY MOVING AWAY, YOUR FUCKING
30TH BIRTHDAY PARTY,

15:53.486 --> 15:56.056
YOU PULL THE ELUSIVE
BRIAN KINNEY BIT AND BAIL.

15:56.089 --> 15:57.490
WHY IS THAT?

15:57.524 --> 15:59.392
- YOU KNOW,
IF THAT'S A RHETORICAL QUESTION

15:59.426 --> 16:01.061
NOT REQUIRING AN ANSWER,

16:01.094 --> 16:03.763
PARDON ME
WHILE I TAKE A LEAK.

16:03.796 --> 16:06.399
- YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK IT IS?

16:06.433 --> 16:08.268
I THINK YOU'RE AFRAID
TO LET ANYONE KNOW

16:08.301 --> 16:10.003
THAT YOU LOVE THEM,

16:10.037 --> 16:14.007
THAT YOU HAVE FEELINGS
LIKE THE REST OF US.

16:14.041 --> 16:17.177
IT'S OKAY TO BE HUMAN,
YOU KNOW.

16:17.210 --> 16:19.446
- OKAY.

16:19.479 --> 16:23.250
YOU REALLY WANT TO KNOW
THE REASON I BAIL?

16:23.283 --> 16:26.519
THE TRUTH IS,
I'D RATHER GET LAID.

16:26.553 --> 16:28.188
- * DANCE

16:28.221 --> 16:31.191
- WE DONE?

16:38.831 --> 16:42.135
- DOES HE ALWAYS
KISS YOU LIKE THAT?

16:42.169 --> 16:44.437
- ABOUT FOUR TIMES A YEAR.

16:44.471 --> 16:45.705
USUALLY WHEN HE'S REALLY DRUNK

16:45.738 --> 16:48.475
OR HE WANTS ME TO SHUT UP.

16:48.508 --> 16:50.243
- AH.

16:54.314 --> 16:56.749
- I STICK IT AND SPIN.

16:56.783 --> 16:58.385
OKAY?
NOW WHEN IT'S READY,

16:58.418 --> 17:00.487
YOU PLATE 'EM, YOU DROP
THE TAB UNDER THE DISH,

17:00.520 --> 17:02.055
YOU THROW IT HERE,
AND THEN YOU RING THE BELL.

17:02.089 --> 17:04.357
[bell rings]
GOT IT?

17:04.391 --> 17:07.227
- STICK IT, SPIN 'EM, DROP 'EM.
[bell rings]

17:07.260 --> 17:08.528
- WHAT'D I TELL YOU?

17:08.561 --> 17:10.730
SHORT ORDERING'S NO DIFFERENT
THAN BEING A CHEF.

17:10.763 --> 17:12.165
- JUST FASTER.

17:12.199 --> 17:15.535
- HEY, WE GOT HUSTLE
IN OUR BLOOD.

17:15.568 --> 17:19.672
OKAY, NOW I'M GOING TO GIVE YOU
YOUR FIRST TIP.

17:19.706 --> 17:22.542
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,
DON'T PANIC.

17:22.575 --> 17:25.145
JUST TAKE YOUR TIME, OKAY?

17:25.178 --> 17:27.114
YOUR WORST
IS FUCKING GOOD ENOUGH

17:27.147 --> 17:28.781
FOR THIS JOINT.

17:28.815 --> 17:32.485
OKAY?

17:32.519 --> 17:34.321
- IT'S NOT SUCH A BIG DEAL.

17:34.354 --> 17:38.358
HEY, DEBBIE. WE NEED A COUPLE
OF BLACK COFFEES TO GO.

17:38.391 --> 17:39.459
- THEY WERE SPECIALLY ENGRAVED

17:39.492 --> 17:42.362
WITH OUR NAMES ON THEM
AND EVERYTHING.

17:45.698 --> 17:47.400
- I HATE TO TELL YOU, GALS,

17:47.434 --> 17:49.202
BUT FOR THE HAPPY COUPLE,

17:49.236 --> 17:50.570
YOU LOOK FUCKING MISERABLE.

17:50.603 --> 17:52.172
- ROSENBERG'S JEWELRY CALLED.

17:52.205 --> 17:54.141
THEY CAN'T FIND
OUR WEDDING RINGS.

17:54.174 --> 17:56.309
- YOU CAN USE
MY NIPPLE RINGS.

17:56.343 --> 17:58.278
LOADS OF SENTIMENTAL VALUE.

17:58.311 --> 17:59.279
TO ME.

17:59.312 --> 18:00.780
- THANKS, HONEY.

18:00.813 --> 18:02.782
BUT IT JUST WOULDN'T BE
THE SAME.

18:02.815 --> 18:04.384
- LISTEN...
- NO.

18:04.417 --> 18:05.252
- WE'RE NOT GOING
TO ALLOW MERCURY

18:05.285 --> 18:07.387
OR ANYTHING ELSE
TO FUCK UP OUR WEDDING.

18:07.420 --> 18:10.590
EVERYTHING'S GOING AHEAD
AS PLANNED.

18:10.623 --> 18:13.560
- UH, NOT EXACTLY EVERYTHING.

18:13.593 --> 18:15.262
- MORE GOOD NEWS?

18:15.295 --> 18:16.729
- BRIAN INVITED ME
TO THE WHITE PARTY.

18:16.763 --> 18:18.565
- AND YOU SAID?

18:18.598 --> 18:21.268
- THAT I'D GO.

18:21.301 --> 18:23.270
IT'S A ONCE
IN A LIFETIME THING.

18:23.303 --> 18:26.606
- SO IS GETTING MARRIED.

18:26.639 --> 18:27.707
'COURSE THERE ARE
NO HARD BODIES.

18:27.740 --> 18:30.343
NO DRUGS, NO THOUSANDS
OF DICKS.

18:30.377 --> 18:33.146
JUST TWO PEOPLE SAYING,
"I DO."

18:33.180 --> 18:36.183
YOU'RE RIGHT,
HOW COULD IT POSSIBLY COMPARE?

18:36.216 --> 18:37.484
- IT'S OKAY.

18:37.517 --> 18:39.186
AFTER ALL JUSTIN'S BEEN
THROUGH.

18:39.219 --> 18:40.587
- YEAH, HE DESERVES A BREAK.

18:40.620 --> 18:44.757
HAVE A GREAT TIME.

18:44.791 --> 18:45.858
- [sighs]

18:45.892 --> 18:48.161
- OH, THAT FUCKING BRIAN.

18:48.195 --> 18:49.629
IT'S BAD ENOUGH HE'S NOT COMING,
DOES HE HAVE TO POACH

18:49.662 --> 18:50.830
OUR RING BEARER AS WELL?

18:50.863 --> 18:52.465
- WHAT DOES IT MATTER?
THERE ARE NO RINGS.

18:52.499 --> 18:55.635
[cell phone rings]
HEY, HONEY.

18:55.668 --> 18:57.504
[phone beeps]
HELLO?

18:57.537 --> 18:58.771
- [woman speaking
indistinctly on phone]

18:58.805 --> 19:00.773
- I'M SORRY, WHAT?

19:00.807 --> 19:03.310
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
- IT MUST BE THE CATERER.

19:03.343 --> 19:05.845
JO, WHAT KOSHER VEGAN DELICACY
HAVE YOU WHIPPED UP?

19:05.878 --> 19:07.514
- I'M SORRY.

19:07.547 --> 19:10.717
- OH, WAIT. LISTEN,
YOU BLEEDING ASSHOLE!

19:10.750 --> 19:12.785
I'M A LAWYER,
WE HAVE A CONTRACT, WE'LL SUE.

19:12.819 --> 19:15.855
- SUE?
- OH, THAT WORD YOU UNDERSTAND.

19:15.888 --> 19:18.458
[phone beeps[
- SOMETHING WRONG?

19:18.491 --> 19:19.492
THE CATERER AND THE HALL

19:19.526 --> 19:20.793
HAVE BEEN SHUT DOWN
BY THE HEALTH DEPARTMENT,

19:20.827 --> 19:22.262
FOR SALMONELLA POISONING.

19:22.295 --> 19:23.430
- [laughs mockingly]

19:23.463 --> 19:25.332
IS THAT ALL? IS THAT ALL.
- IS THAT ALL? IS THAT ALL?

19:25.365 --> 19:27.367
WE HAVE NO FOOD, WE HAVE
NO PLACE TO EAT THE FOOD.

19:27.400 --> 19:28.535
- [hyperventilating]

19:28.568 --> 19:30.770
OKAY, IF YOU DON'T MIND,

19:30.803 --> 19:32.539
I THINK I'LL LIE DOWN FOR A BIT,
OKAY?

19:32.572 --> 19:37.577
- YEAH.
- [rapid panting]

19:38.711 --> 19:42.815
- YOU SPENT $500--
MY $500 ON THAT?

19:42.849 --> 19:43.950
- IT WAS A STEAL.

19:43.983 --> 19:45.352
- YEAH, AND I'M THE ONE
THAT GOT ROBBED.

19:45.385 --> 19:46.353
LOOK, JUST TAKE IT BACK.

19:46.386 --> 19:47.620
- I CAN'T TAKE IT BACK.

19:47.654 --> 19:48.788
WHAT STORE DID YOU BUY IT AT?

19:48.821 --> 19:50.690
- I DIDN'T GET IT AT A STORE.

19:50.723 --> 19:51.691
- WHERE'D YOU GET IT?

19:51.724 --> 19:52.692
- OFF A BLANKET.

19:52.725 --> 19:54.761
- A BLANKET?

19:54.794 --> 19:56.629
YOU BOUGHT LINDSAY
AND MELANIE'S WEDDING GIFT

19:56.663 --> 19:58.265
FROM SOME STREET CORNER
SHYSTER?

19:58.298 --> 19:59.366
- IT'S FROM CHUCK.

19:59.399 --> 20:00.800
IT'S A LITTLE COUNTRY
NEXT TO CHAD.

20:00.833 --> 20:02.902
- CHUCK? CHAD? THEY SOUND LIKE
A COUPLE OF HOMOS.

20:02.935 --> 20:04.304
- IT'S THE PERFECT GIFT.

20:04.337 --> 20:05.972
- PERFECTLY HIDEOUS.
- IT'S A WORK OF ART!

20:06.005 --> 20:06.773
- IT'S A PIECE OF SHIT.

20:06.806 --> 20:08.908
- IT'S SYMBOLIC
OF LOVE AND PRIDE.

20:08.941 --> 20:10.977
- IT'S SYMBOLIC OF STUPIDITY
AND BAD TASTE.

20:11.010 --> 20:11.778
- YOU TAKE THAT BACK.

20:11.811 --> 20:14.281
- I CAN'T.
I GOT IT OFF A BLANKET.

20:14.314 --> 20:15.648
- LOOK, THE NEXT TIME
YOU WANT TO BUY A GIFT,

20:15.682 --> 20:16.849
BUY IT YOURSELF.

20:16.883 --> 20:18.551
- THAT'S WHAT
I WAS COUNTING ON YOU FOR.

20:18.585 --> 20:21.321
- YEAH, YOU WERE TOO BUSY
BRINGING JOY TO THE WORLD.

20:21.354 --> 20:22.422
- LOOK, JUST BECAUSE
I'M A SUCCESS--

20:22.455 --> 20:23.423
- YOU CAN TAKE YOUR SUCCESS

20:23.456 --> 20:24.591
AND SHOVE IT.

20:24.624 --> 20:25.592
AND I'M SURE YOU WON'T
HAVE ANY TROUBLE

20:25.625 --> 20:26.826
FIGURING OUT WHERE.

20:26.859 --> 20:31.564
- YEAH, I'LL JUST ASK
CHUCK AND CHAD.

20:35.768 --> 20:38.438
- I'M SORRY, GEORGE.

20:38.471 --> 20:40.307
I'VE MADE UP MY MIND.

20:40.340 --> 20:43.610
- BUT IT'S SUCH A...

20:43.643 --> 20:45.345
BEAUTIFUL BOTTOM.

20:45.378 --> 20:46.813
- IT'LL DO IN A PINCH.

20:46.846 --> 20:47.980
- I'LL SAY.

20:48.014 --> 20:49.749
BESIDES, YOU'RE TOO YOUNG.

20:49.782 --> 20:53.019
I MEAN, PLASTIC SURGERY
IS JUST FOR FOOLISH OLD MEN

20:53.052 --> 20:57.990
WHO REFUSE TO GROW OLD
GRACEFULLY.

20:58.024 --> 20:59.692
- WHAT ABOUT MICHAEL JACKSON?

20:59.726 --> 21:02.695
AND ELIZABETH TAYLOR
AND CHER?

21:02.729 --> 21:05.865
- WELL, I CAN'T SPEAK
FOR THEIR BACKSIDES,

21:05.898 --> 21:07.367
ONLY YOURS.

21:07.400 --> 21:08.901
- THANK YOU.

21:08.935 --> 21:11.504
BUT IN MY WORLD,
IF YOU DON'T LOOK LIKE YOU

21:11.538 --> 21:14.006
JUST STEPPED OUT OF
A CALVIN KLEIN UNDERWEAR AD,

21:14.040 --> 21:15.842
YOU'RE NOTHING.

21:15.875 --> 21:18.378
- WELL, THAT'S A WORLD
I'M HAPPY NOT TO KNOW.

21:18.411 --> 21:20.313
- NOT TO MENTION,

21:20.347 --> 21:22.048
IT'LL MAKE ME FEEL BETTER
ABOUT MYSELF.

21:22.081 --> 21:25.352
YOU KNOW,
RAISE MY SELF-ESTEEM.

21:25.385 --> 21:27.920
- WELL, MY WIFE VIRGINIA
FELT SIMILARLY.

21:27.954 --> 21:30.890
HAD HERSELF SNIPPED AND CLIPPED,
EYES TO THIGHS.

21:30.923 --> 21:32.892
SWORE IT WOULD
CHANGE HER LIFE TOO.

21:32.925 --> 21:34.661
- AND DID IT?

21:34.694 --> 21:37.029
- SHE WAS THE SAME MISERABLE
CUNT SHE ALWAYS WAS.

21:37.063 --> 21:40.333
ONLY WITHOUT THE WRINKLES.

21:40.367 --> 21:42.001
NOW EMMETT...

21:42.034 --> 21:43.636
FORGIVE ME.

21:43.670 --> 21:48.641
BUT ANYONE WHO VALUES THEMSELVES
BECAUSE OF THEIR ASS...

21:48.675 --> 21:51.578
IS AN ASS.

21:54.581 --> 21:55.815
[overlapping chatter]

21:55.848 --> 21:57.083
- OH, I'M SO SORRY
YOU'RE STILL WAITING.

21:57.116 --> 21:58.518
MORE COFFEE?
IT'S ON THE HOUSE.

21:58.551 --> 22:00.420
NO?
OKAY.

22:00.453 --> 22:03.823
UM, YOUR ORDER IS NEXT,
I PROMISE YOU.

22:03.856 --> 22:06.959
- ALL I WANT IS A HAMBURGER!

22:06.993 --> 22:10.363
- YOUR ORDER HAS BEEN
ABDUCTED BY ALIENS,

22:10.397 --> 22:12.432
SO DON'T GIVE ME
THOSE DIRTY LOOKS.

22:12.465 --> 22:14.401
[dishes clatter]

22:14.434 --> 22:15.702
- HEY, DEBBIE,
WHAT'S UP WITH MY ORDER?

22:15.735 --> 22:16.703
[bell rings]

22:16.736 --> 22:18.405
- HEY!

22:18.438 --> 22:20.707
I HAVE GOT ORDERS COMING
OUT MY ASS,

22:20.740 --> 22:23.042
A ROOM FULL
OF HUNGRY HOMICIDALS,

22:23.075 --> 22:24.577
AND I DON'T HAVE
ANY CLEAN PLATES

22:24.611 --> 22:25.978
TO DO MY SET-UPS WITH.

22:26.012 --> 22:27.947
WHAT IN THE FUCK
IS GOING ON BACK HERE?

22:27.980 --> 22:29.649
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO YELL.

22:29.682 --> 22:30.850
I'M RIGHT HERE.

22:30.883 --> 22:31.818
- WELL, YOU COULD HAVE
FOOLED ME.

22:31.851 --> 22:33.720
DO YOU THINK YOU COULD
DO A GRILLED CHEESE

22:33.753 --> 22:34.921
IN UNDER AN HOUR?

22:34.954 --> 22:38.858
- YOU TOLD ME TO TAKE MY TIME.
- DEBBIE!

22:38.891 --> 22:40.727
- I DIDN'T MEAN
YOUR FUCKING LIFETIME.

22:40.760 --> 22:44.397
- [sighs]
THAT DOES IT.

22:44.431 --> 22:45.798
- EXCUSE ME.
- WHO AM I KIDDING?

22:45.832 --> 22:46.933
- EXCUSE ME!
- I CAN'T DO THIS.

22:46.966 --> 22:48.668
- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

22:48.701 --> 22:49.669
HOME.

22:49.702 --> 22:51.438
- YOU CAN'T LEAVE ME LIKE THIS.

22:51.471 --> 22:52.672
- YOU'RE BETTER OFF.

22:52.705 --> 22:55.608
I'M USELESS.
I'M WORSE THAN USELESS.

22:55.642 --> 22:57.844
I'M RIDICULOUS.
- TEN MORE MINUTES, I PROMISE.

22:57.877 --> 22:59.412
- WE'RE HUNGRY!

22:59.446 --> 23:02.715
- HONEY, THERE IS NO WAY
WE CAN SQUEEZE

23:02.749 --> 23:04.617
THAT MANY GUESTS
INTO OUR HOUSE.

23:04.651 --> 23:07.119
- BABY, WE CAN MOVE ALL
THE FURNITURE INTO THE GARAGE.

23:07.153 --> 23:11.691
- LAMBSKIN, YOU'D HAVE
MY 1,000-YEAR-OLD AUNT

23:11.724 --> 23:12.959
STAND ALL NIGHT?

23:12.992 --> 23:15.094
- PUDDING PIE,
SHE HAS A WALKER.

23:15.127 --> 23:16.429
SHE CAN LEAN.

23:16.463 --> 23:18.631
- AND WHAT IF, SOMEHOW,

23:18.665 --> 23:21.033
MY LITTLE LOVE BUTTON,

23:21.067 --> 23:24.170
WE MANAGE TO OVERCOME THE LAWS
OF PHYSICAL SCIENCE

23:24.203 --> 23:25.705
AND PACK 'EM ALL IN?

23:25.738 --> 23:27.907
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE THEY GOING TO SEE

23:27.940 --> 23:29.609
BESIDES EACH OTHERS'
NOSE HAIR?

23:29.642 --> 23:31.478
- YOU'RE NOT EVEN TRYING
TO MAKE THIS WORK.

23:31.511 --> 23:33.513
- AND YOU'RE NOT EVEN TRYING
TO MAKE SENSE.

23:33.546 --> 23:34.881
- THERE'S NO NEED TO BE ABUSIVE.

23:34.914 --> 23:36.716
- I WASN'T BEING ABUSIVE.

23:36.749 --> 23:39.652
I WAS MERELY EXPRESSING...

23:39.686 --> 23:40.653
FRUSTRATION.

23:40.687 --> 23:41.721
- SO NOW I'M FRUSTRATING?

23:41.754 --> 23:43.490
- I DIDN'T SAY THAT.
[groans]

23:43.523 --> 23:44.491
[knock on door]

23:44.524 --> 23:46.926
- CLEANING'S HERE. AH.

23:48.961 --> 23:51.163
- YOURS, MEL.

23:51.197 --> 23:54.901
AND WHAT WAS YOURS, LINZ.

23:54.934 --> 23:57.804
APPARENTLY THE DRY-CLEANING
SOLUTION WAS TOO--

23:57.837 --> 24:02.074
- THERE'S NO NEED TO EXPLAIN.

24:02.108 --> 24:07.013
AT THIS POINT IN THE PLOT,
WE ALL GET IT.

24:07.046 --> 24:08.080
- BUT THE GOOD NEWS IS,

24:08.114 --> 24:11.751
THEY GAVE YOU $100 WORTH
OF COUPONS.

24:11.784 --> 24:13.152
- HURRAY.

24:13.185 --> 24:17.490
- WE WILL FIND YOU SOMETHING
ELSE TO WEAR, BOO-BOO.

24:17.524 --> 24:19.626
AND WE WILL HAVE
OUR BEAUTIFUL,

24:19.659 --> 24:22.228
SPECIAL FUCKING DAY,
GODDAMN IT!

24:22.261 --> 24:26.165
EVEN IF WE HAVE TO DO IT NUDE
IN THE BACKYARD.

24:26.198 --> 24:29.536
[thunder rumbles]

24:29.569 --> 24:30.537
[Gus crying]

24:30.570 --> 24:34.707
- OR MAYBE WE CAN FACE REALITY.

24:34.741 --> 24:36.676
MYSTERIOUS MARILYN WAS RIGHT.

24:36.709 --> 24:40.580
- OH, NOT THAT MERCURY
IN RETROGRADE SHIT AGAIN.

24:40.613 --> 24:42.181
- OUR WEDDING'S
BEEN METHODICALLY

24:42.214 --> 24:44.216
AND SYSTEMATICALLY
DECONSTRUCTED.

24:44.250 --> 24:47.086
IF YOU ASK ME,
SOMEBODY UP THERE

24:47.119 --> 24:50.557
DOESN'T THINK
WE SHOULD GET MARRIED.

24:50.590 --> 24:53.993
MAYBE THERE'S A REASON.

24:54.026 --> 24:58.998
MAYBE THAT'S BECAUSE
PEOPLE LIKE US...

24:59.031 --> 25:00.700
AREN'T SUPPOSED TO GET MARRIED.

25:00.733 --> 25:02.068
- "LIKE US"?

25:02.101 --> 25:03.235
- DO YOU NEED THE ROOF
TO CAVE IN?

25:03.269 --> 25:06.639
[crying continues]

25:15.615 --> 25:18.585
[eerie music]

25:18.618 --> 25:26.525
*

25:37.069 --> 25:41.107
- YOU KNOW, I'M REMINDED
OF A SCENE FROM ALIEN.

25:41.140 --> 25:44.777
ONE OF THE GREAT AIDS METAPHOR
FLICKS OF ALL TIME.

25:44.811 --> 25:47.046
OUR INTREPID INTERGALACTIC
GARBAGE COLLECTORS,

25:47.079 --> 25:49.649
LED BY UBER-BITCH DYKE RIPLEY,

25:49.682 --> 25:52.785
AFTER WHO YOU'VE OBVIOUSLY
MODELED YOURSELF,

25:52.819 --> 25:55.321
ARE SNUGGLED SAFELY
IN THEIR SLEEP PODS

25:55.354 --> 25:57.189
FOR THE LONG RIDE HOME

25:57.223 --> 25:59.792
WHEN SUDDENLY
THE MONSTER APPEARS.

25:59.826 --> 26:01.928
- THE WEDDING'S OFF.

26:01.961 --> 26:04.864
- YOU TWO HAVE FINALLY COME
TO YOUR SENSES?

26:04.897 --> 26:06.799
THAT'S ALMOST REASON ENOUGH

26:06.833 --> 26:08.868
TO INTERRUPT MY BASE COAT.

26:08.901 --> 26:12.004
BUT NOT QUITE.

26:12.038 --> 26:14.073
- IT'S BECAUSE OF LINDSAY.

26:14.106 --> 26:16.142
SHE--
[sobs]

26:16.175 --> 26:17.343
SHE...

26:17.376 --> 26:19.211
- SHE WHAT?

26:19.245 --> 26:24.050
- WITH ALL THE DISASTERS
AND MYSTERIOUS MARILYN,

26:24.083 --> 26:27.219
MERCURY IN RETROGRADE
AND THE RINGS AND THE FOOD

26:27.253 --> 26:30.322
AND THE HALL AND THE DRESS,

26:30.356 --> 26:32.358
SHE THINKS THE WEDDING'S NOT
SUPPOSED TO HAPPEN BECAUSE--

26:32.391 --> 26:35.361
BECAUSE WE'RE GAY.

26:35.394 --> 26:37.897
- CHRIST.

26:37.930 --> 26:43.102
SEND IN A DYKE
TO DO A FAGGOT'S WORK.

26:43.135 --> 26:46.072
WE HAVE PRECISELY 21 HOURS

26:46.105 --> 26:48.174
TO GET THE MUNCHERS MARRIED.

26:48.207 --> 26:50.810
- WHAT? ARE YOU CRAZY?
- WE CAN'T DO THAT.

26:50.843 --> 26:52.779
- NOBODY KNOWS WEDDING SHIT
BETTER THAN QUEERS.

26:52.812 --> 26:54.714
WE'RE THE FLORISTS,
THE CATERERS,

26:54.747 --> 26:56.783
THE PLANNERS, THE DESIGNERS.

26:56.816 --> 27:00.252
THE SERVERS, THE PERFORMERS,
EVEN FUCKING PRIESTS.

27:00.286 --> 27:01.988
- HE MEANS THAT LITERALLY.

27:02.021 --> 27:03.022
- IF ANYBODY CAN DO IT,
WE CAN.

27:03.055 --> 27:06.325
AND WE WILL, IN TIME FOR ME
TO MAKE MY FLIGHT.

27:06.358 --> 27:08.094
- DON'T YOU THINK
THIS IS AWFULLY AMBITIOUS?

27:08.127 --> 27:09.028
- WHY DON'T
YOU JUST LEAVE IT UP

27:09.061 --> 27:10.730
TO EVERYBODY ELSE
SO YOU CAN CRITICIZE?

27:10.763 --> 27:11.864
- IF WE LEFT IT UP TO YOU,

27:11.898 --> 27:13.265
THEY'D BE GETTING MARRIED
ON A BLANKET

27:13.299 --> 27:14.734
ON A STREET CORNER.
- YO, BITCHES,

27:14.767 --> 27:16.135
TEAR EACH OTHER'S
HAIR OUT LATER.

27:16.168 --> 27:17.336
I DON'T CARE HOW YOU DO IT,

27:17.369 --> 27:19.405
BUT YOU TWO ARE RESPONSIBLE
FOR STAFFING,

27:19.438 --> 27:21.841
FLOWERS, AND DECORATIONS.

27:21.874 --> 27:24.210
- EMMETT, YOU FIND US A PLACE.

27:24.243 --> 27:26.145
- OH, HOW ABOUT
THE LIBERTY BATHS?

27:26.178 --> 27:29.682
THEY HAVE
A FABULOUS PARTY ROOM.

27:29.716 --> 27:33.019
- DEB, YOU PULL TOGETHER
SOMETHING FOR LINZ TO WEAR.

27:33.052 --> 27:34.687
- I'D LOVE TO.

27:34.721 --> 27:37.123
OH, I CAN JUST SEE IT
WITH ITS FLOWERS

27:37.156 --> 27:41.027
AND BOWS AND RUFFLES AND--

27:41.060 --> 27:44.430
MAYBE SOMETHING MORE SIMPLE.

27:44.463 --> 27:45.965
- VIC, YOU'RE UP FOR THE CAKE.

27:45.998 --> 27:48.234
- NO, MY COOKING'S
A RECIPE FOR DISASTER.

27:48.267 --> 27:49.902
- HE'D BE GREAT...

27:49.936 --> 27:53.139
IF THEY WERE GETTING MARRIED
A YEAR FROM NOW.

27:53.172 --> 27:54.440
- DON'T WORRY, VIC.
I'LL HELP YOU.

27:54.473 --> 27:57.309
- OKAY, GREAT. GET TO WORK.

27:57.343 --> 27:58.711
- NOW HOLD IT, KINNEY.

27:58.745 --> 28:00.446
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

28:00.479 --> 28:04.050
- I'M GETTING MY BEAUTY REST.
BYE-BYE.

28:04.083 --> 28:05.184
- [laughs]

28:05.217 --> 28:08.120
[overlapping chatter]

28:08.154 --> 28:12.925
- OH, NOT TONIGHT, DEAR.
I'M SAVING MYSELF FOR MIAMI.

28:12.959 --> 28:14.160
- CORRECT ME IF I'M WRONG,

28:14.193 --> 28:15.427
BUT I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T GIVE

28:15.461 --> 28:16.763
A SHIT ABOUT YOUR FRIENDS,

28:16.796 --> 28:18.430
THAT YOU ONLY CARE
ABOUT GETTING LAID.

28:18.464 --> 28:21.801
- I JUST NEVER WANT TO HEAR
THE WORD "WEDDING" AGAIN.

28:21.834 --> 28:24.170
- YOU'RE PATHETIC.

28:24.203 --> 28:25.738
- OH, EMMETT, DO YOU WANT
TO GO WITH ME

28:25.772 --> 28:27.073
TO GET MATERIAL?

28:27.106 --> 28:31.277
- UH, HELLO.
ZANZIBAR. YEAH.

28:31.310 --> 28:34.080
YES, I'D LIKE TO BOOK A WEDDING
IN YOUR PRIVATE ROOM.

28:34.113 --> 28:36.448
- YES, OF COURSE.
WE CAN DO THAT, NO PROBLEM.

28:36.482 --> 28:38.785
- YOU CAN?
OH, YOU CAN.

28:38.818 --> 28:40.286
OH, GOD. WONDERFUL.

28:40.319 --> 28:44.223
OKAY. RIGHT, WELL,
THAT WILL BE FOR ABOUT 80.

28:44.256 --> 28:46.492
MM-HMM.
RIGHT. TONIGHT.

28:46.525 --> 28:49.829
- TONIGHT?
[laughs]

28:49.862 --> 28:52.364
[phone beeps]

28:52.398 --> 28:53.833
- ANY LUCK?

28:53.866 --> 28:56.202
- I HAVE TRIED
"A" THROUGH "Z."

28:56.235 --> 28:58.504
I'M AFRAID
THERE IS NO SUCH THING

28:58.537 --> 29:01.207
AS AN INSTANT WEDDING.

29:01.240 --> 29:03.309
- IF I MAY MAKE A SUGGESTION?

29:03.342 --> 29:06.112
- BE MY WEDDING GUEST.

29:06.145 --> 29:07.513
- WELL, IT'S NOT VERY TRENDY,

29:07.546 --> 29:09.515
BUT THE PRICE IS RIGHT.

29:09.548 --> 29:12.518
[classical music]

29:12.551 --> 29:16.355
*

29:16.388 --> 29:18.190
- HOLY XANADU.

29:18.224 --> 29:21.794
- WELL, LAST TIME IT WAS USED,

29:21.828 --> 29:24.330
IT WAS MY DAUGHTER
FRANKIE'S WEDDING.

29:24.363 --> 29:25.865
- "FRANKIE"?

29:25.898 --> 29:27.533
- YEAH, VIRGINIA NAMED HER
AFTER HAMMOND MEATS'

29:27.566 --> 29:29.135
MOST POPULAR PRODUCT.

29:29.168 --> 29:30.970
[chuckles]

29:31.003 --> 29:33.239
GOSH, IT WAS ONE OF
THE HAPPIEST DAYS OF MY LIFE.

29:33.272 --> 29:34.473
- WELL, IT SOUNDS TO ME, HONEY,

29:34.506 --> 29:36.976
LIKE THIS PLACE IS DUE
FOR A PARTY.

29:37.009 --> 29:39.078
- I COULDN'T THINK OF
A MORE APPROPRIATE OCCASION

29:39.111 --> 29:40.012
THAN YOUR FRIENDS' WEDDING.

29:40.046 --> 29:43.215
I'LL FILL THIS ROOM
WITH EXOTIC FLOWERS.

29:43.249 --> 29:44.483
I'LL BRING
IN THE PITTSBURGH SYMPHONY.

29:44.516 --> 29:47.019
I'M ON THE BOARD.
- UM--

29:47.053 --> 29:49.088
THAT'S VERY KIND,
AS USUAL.

29:49.121 --> 29:53.025
BUT I'D KIND OF LIKE
TO TAKE CARE OF THIS MYSELF.

29:53.059 --> 29:56.262
YOU KNOW, GIVE MEL AND LINDSAY
THE MOST FABULOUS WEDDING

29:56.295 --> 29:57.563
TWO GIRLS EVER HAD.

29:57.596 --> 30:00.432
- THAT'S ALSO VERY KIND.
AS USUAL.

30:00.466 --> 30:03.836
HOW CAN YOU AFFORD TO?

30:03.870 --> 30:06.906
- MY TUSH FUND.

30:08.908 --> 30:11.043
- YOU'D BURST
YOUR BUBBLE-BUTT DREAM?

30:11.077 --> 30:14.146
- WELL, IF YOU DON'T MIND
A BUMPY RIDE,

30:14.180 --> 30:17.083
I THINK THIS OLD THING'S GOT
A FEW MORE MILES ON IT.

30:17.116 --> 30:18.217
- OH, MY GOD.

30:18.250 --> 30:21.220
[both laugh]
- MWAH.

30:23.255 --> 30:25.057
- THANK YOU.

30:25.091 --> 30:27.059
NOW, I HAVE TO GET STARTED.

30:27.093 --> 30:28.928
I SHOULD HAVE BEEN UP
TO MY TITS

30:28.961 --> 30:31.931
IN TULLE AND TWINKLING LIGHTS
HOURS AGO!

30:31.964 --> 30:35.167
[giggles]

30:35.201 --> 30:40.106
[sewing machine whirs]

30:41.273 --> 30:42.909
- OH, SHIT!

30:42.942 --> 30:44.210
- WHAT HAPPENED?

30:44.243 --> 30:46.245
- NOTHING.

30:46.278 --> 30:48.580
[cup clatters]
FUCK!

30:48.614 --> 30:50.349
- NOW WHAT?

30:50.382 --> 30:53.352
- IT'S ME, DEB.
I'M A KLUTZ.

30:55.254 --> 30:58.124
- YOU'D THINK I'D NEVER SET FOOT
IN A KITCHEN BEFORE.

30:58.157 --> 30:59.992
- YOU JUST NEED TO RELAX.

31:00.026 --> 31:01.227
- IT'S MORE THAN THAT.

31:01.260 --> 31:02.962
I'VE BEEN OUT OF THE WORLD
TOO LONG.

31:02.995 --> 31:04.196
I CAN'T GO BACK.

31:04.230 --> 31:06.265
- YOU'RE RIGHT, YOU CAN'T.

31:06.298 --> 31:09.268
CHRIST, WOULD YOU LOOK
AT THIS MESS.

31:09.301 --> 31:12.238
YOU ARE THE FUCKING SADDEST
HARD-LUCK CASE

31:12.271 --> 31:13.605
I HAVE EVER SEEN.

31:13.639 --> 31:16.475
- DEBBIE.
- GET BACK IN YOUR ROBE, HUH?

31:16.508 --> 31:19.111
OR BETTER YET,
FIND A TRAIN TO FALL UNDER.

31:19.145 --> 31:21.413
AT LEAST I'D GET THE INSURANCE.

31:21.447 --> 31:23.649
SUNSHINE, GET YOUR JACKET.
LET'S GO.

31:23.682 --> 31:24.984
- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

31:25.017 --> 31:26.285
- WHERE DO YOU THINK?

31:26.318 --> 31:27.419
TO THE BAKERY.

31:27.453 --> 31:28.487
YOU PROMISED THE GIRLS

31:28.520 --> 31:30.022
A WEDDING CAKE, DIDN'T YOU?

31:30.056 --> 31:31.690
- YOU CAN'T JUST STROLL
INTO A BAKERY

31:31.723 --> 31:34.260
AND BUY A WEDDING CAKE,
THEY'RE MADE SPECIAL.

31:34.293 --> 31:36.996
- SO, WE'LL GET 'EM
A BON VOYAGE CAKE

31:37.029 --> 31:38.497
OR A BIRTHDAY CAKE

31:38.530 --> 31:40.566
OR A FUCKING
BAR MITZVAH CAKE!

31:40.599 --> 31:43.535
ANY CAKE WILL BE BETTER
THAN THE DRIED-OUT BRICK

31:43.569 --> 31:46.572
THAT YOU'RE PLANNING.

31:51.277 --> 31:55.114
- HOW DARE YOU CALL
MY HAZELNUT BUTTERCREAM

31:55.147 --> 31:57.916
A DRIED-OUT BRICK?

32:08.194 --> 32:11.330
- [humming]

32:19.571 --> 32:21.440
- YOU DID ALL THAT ON PURPOSE,
DIDN'T YOU?

32:21.473 --> 32:25.744
- HOW DO YOU THINK I GOT HIM
TO LIVE IN THE FIRST PLACE?

32:25.777 --> 32:30.582
I JUST KEPT SCREAMING,
"SO FUCKING DIE ALREADY!"

32:30.616 --> 32:32.218
WORKED LIKE A CHARM.

32:32.251 --> 32:35.221
- HE NEVER FIGURED IT OUT?

32:35.254 --> 32:37.589
- APPARENTLY NOT.

32:37.623 --> 32:39.091
- JUSTIN,

32:39.125 --> 32:40.326
I NEED
THESE EGG WHITES BEATEN.

32:40.359 --> 32:43.329
- AND AS FOR YOU...

32:43.362 --> 32:45.364
YOU WANT TO GROW UP
TO BE ANOTHER BRIAN KINNEY?

32:45.397 --> 32:48.067
ALWAYS RUNNING AWAY FROM LOVE,
NEVER TOWARDS IT?

32:48.100 --> 32:49.335
THEN YOU GO TO MIAMI

32:49.368 --> 32:51.203
AND YOU FUCK
YOUR LITTLE TWINKIE BRAINS OUT.

32:51.237 --> 32:53.639
BUT IT'S NEVER GONNA
MAKE YOU HAPPY.

32:53.672 --> 32:56.208
- [chuckles]
NICE TRY, DEBBIE.

32:56.242 --> 33:01.480
- WAIT A MINUTE.

33:01.513 --> 33:03.449
ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE ON TO ME.

33:03.482 --> 33:05.184
BUT ONE DAY YOU'RE GOING
TO LOOK BACK,

33:05.217 --> 33:09.521
AND YOU'RE GOING TO REGRET THAT
YOU DIDN'T GO TO THE WEDDING...

33:09.555 --> 33:12.358
WITH YOUR FAMILY.

33:12.391 --> 33:15.261
AND THAT'S THE TRUTH,
SUNSHINE.

33:15.294 --> 33:18.130
THAT'S THE TRUTH.

33:30.309 --> 33:33.279
- FRENCH TOAST
WITH FRESH STRAWBERRIES.

33:33.312 --> 33:35.681
BACON CRUMBLES
AND REAL MAPLE SYRUP.

33:35.714 --> 33:40.286
COFFEE MADE
WITH THE REALLY GOOD BEANS.

33:40.319 --> 33:42.521
AND PEACHES
WITH THE SKIN PEELED OFF

33:42.554 --> 33:44.756
'CAUSE THE LITTLE HAIRS
MAKE YOUR TEETH ITCH.

33:44.790 --> 33:46.258
- NO, THANKS.

33:46.292 --> 33:48.160
- BABY, PLEASE,
YOU HAVE TO EAT.

33:48.194 --> 33:49.661
- WHAT FOR?

33:49.695 --> 33:51.530
- YOU NEED TO KEEP YOUR STRENGTH
UP TO FEEL MISERABLE.

33:51.563 --> 33:53.265
HAVE A STRAWBERRY.

33:53.299 --> 33:54.433
- NO.

33:54.466 --> 33:56.402
- COME ON, BOO-BOO.
ONE LITTLE BITE.

33:56.435 --> 33:58.637
- STOP IT!
- STOP WHAT?

33:58.670 --> 34:00.239
- BEING SO SWEET.

34:00.272 --> 34:01.407
- I CAN'T HELP IT.

34:01.440 --> 34:03.409
COMPULSIVE ADORABLE DISORDER.

34:03.442 --> 34:05.544
- ALL RIGHT, GET UP.

34:05.577 --> 34:07.179
- WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

34:07.213 --> 34:08.314
- COME ON, MOVE YOUR ASSES.

34:08.347 --> 34:11.150
- WHAT FOR?
- YOU'RE GETTING MARRIED.

34:11.183 --> 34:13.152
- HUH?
[shrieks]

34:19.891 --> 34:21.827
- COME ON, GET OUT.

34:21.860 --> 34:23.462
COME ON, GET OUT.
- WHERE THE HELL ARE WE?

34:23.495 --> 34:25.664
- GET OUT, GET OUT.
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

34:25.697 --> 34:28.700
- MS. MARCUS, MS. PETERSON.

34:28.734 --> 34:30.669
WELCOME TO YOUR WEDDING.

34:30.702 --> 34:33.339
ALLOW ME TO INTRODUCE
OUR GRACIOUS HOST,

34:33.372 --> 34:35.807
MY DEAR, DEAR FRIEND,
GEORGE SCHICKEL.

34:35.841 --> 34:38.144
both: SCHICKEL'S PICKLES?

34:38.177 --> 34:41.713
- THE PLEASURE'S MINE.
AND MY HOME IS YOURS TODAY.

34:41.747 --> 34:43.549
- OKAY, ENOUGH CHAT. YOU'RE
BOTH DUE IN HAIR AND MAKE-UP,

34:43.582 --> 34:44.616
SO LET'S GET A MOVE ON.

34:44.650 --> 34:46.318
[overlapping chatter]

34:46.352 --> 34:48.487
- GO!

34:48.520 --> 34:49.555
- OH, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

34:49.588 --> 34:51.323
YOU'RE NOT BRINGING
THAT HIDEOUS THING IN HERE.

34:51.357 --> 34:52.624
- I MOST CERTAINLY AM.

34:52.658 --> 34:54.226
- NOT IF I HAVE ANYTHING
TO SAY ABOUT IT.

34:54.260 --> 34:56.462
- WELL, WHO GIVES A SHIT
WHAT YOU HAVE TO SAY ABOUT IT?

34:56.495 --> 34:58.730
- I'M THE ONE WHO PAID
FOR THAT WASTE OF WOOD.

34:58.764 --> 35:00.199
- WELL, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

35:00.232 --> 35:01.333
I'M GONNA PAY YOU BACK
AND I'M GONNA GIVE IT

35:01.367 --> 35:02.534
TO THE GIRLS MYSELF.

35:02.568 --> 35:03.435
WHAT DO YOU THINK ABOUT THAT?
- I THINK YOU'RE AN IDIOT

35:03.469 --> 35:04.236
FOR PICKING IT OUT
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

35:04.270 --> 35:06.172
- WELL, I THINK
YOU'RE A DICKHEAD

35:06.205 --> 35:07.206
FOR MAKING ME FEEL
LIKE AN IDIOT.

35:07.239 --> 35:08.640
- BOYS. BOYS.

35:08.674 --> 35:11.877
WE STILL SQUABBLING OVER
THE SILLY STATUE?

35:11.910 --> 35:14.713
GOD, SHE MUST HAVE BEEN
TO DR. BEAMER.

35:14.746 --> 35:17.383
- AH, YOU SEE? EMMETT AGREES.
IT'S AN ABOMINATION.

35:17.416 --> 35:19.351
- I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

35:19.385 --> 35:20.419
ALTHOUGH I WILL SAY

35:20.452 --> 35:23.255
IT'S NOT WORTH DESTROYING
YOUR FRIENDSHIP OVER.

35:33.799 --> 35:35.634
- NO, NO, DEBBIE,
I DO MY OWN HAIR.

35:35.667 --> 35:37.636
- I CAN TELL.
- [laughs]

35:37.669 --> 35:39.505
- YOU NEED MORE BELLA DONNA.

35:39.538 --> 35:40.906
LESS BITCHY BUTCHY.
